Commuters may still face delays or revised services following the earlier problems at Glasgow Central. Signalling problems at city station cause delays for commuters Commuters may still face delays or revised services following the earlier problems at Glasgow Central.Despite the issue now being resolved, delays and revisions are expected until 10.00am on Wednesday October 29.The issues at the city centre transport hub are affecting travel to the west, particularly to Largs, Gourock, Wemyss Bay, Ayr and Paisley Canal.Passengers are advised to check services as some may still be cancelled or changed from the normal schedule. 